Reasoning: The paper discusses a novel computing paradigm that is inspired by the brain and uses hyperdimensional (HD) computing. This falls under the category of neural networks and artificial intelligence, which are covered by the cs.NE and cs.NEURAL sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of nanotechnologies such as carbon nanotube field effect transistors (CNFETs) and resistive RAM (RRAM), which are covered by the cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of data representations and embeddings, which are covered by the cs.EMBEDDING sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the HD computing nanosystem using monolithic 3D integration, which falls under the cs.AR (Architecture) sub-category.
